## Spec-Driven Development (spec-kit)
When a project contains `.specify/`, it is source-of-truth: `/speckit.constitution → /speckit.specify → /speckit.clarify → /speckit.plan → /speckit.tasks → /speckit.analyze → /speckit.implement`. No feature code without a spec.

Pairs with superpowers: `brainstorming` → `/speckit.specify` → `test-driven-development` → `/speckit.implement`.

## Memory Protocol (LLM-Wiki second brain)
- Canonical shared vault: **`C:\AI\brain`** via memory-mcp (all agents). Local `MEMORY.md` / `memory/` under this agent home are optional skeletons only.
- `memory/{user,feedback,project,reference}/` at `C:\AI\brain` hold one fact per file (YAML frontmatter, `[[wikilinks]]`); load via MCP on demand.
- `MEMORY.md` and `memory/hot.md` at `C:\AI\brain` are **generated** — never hand-edit. Prefer `memory_write` MCP (auto index/hot/lint).
- Run-logs → `logs/`; telemetry → `telemetry/` — never `memory/`. One learning per file; verify facts before acting.
